# PacketcraftR 0.2.0-rc.1

Source commit: `{{SOURCE_COMMIT}}`

Workspace archive SHA-256: `{{ARCHIVE_SHA256}}`

Post-publication downloaded-artifact smoke evidence: {{SMOKE_EVIDENCE}}

This release candidate is the GitHub-only rehearsal for PacketcraftR 0.2.0.
The public Rust façade, 14-command CLI grammar and exit classes, packet/output
schemas, portable wire behavior, and fixture corpus remain frozen from Beta.

## Distribution

GitHub Releases are the only distribution channel. The attached
`packetcraftr-workspace-0.2.0-rc.1.tar.gz` is the complete buildable workspace;
`SHA256SUMS` authenticates it. All five Cargo packages retain
`publish = false`; nothing is published to crates.io, docs.rs, or another
public registry. The MSRV is Rust 1.96.0.

Install the portable CLI from the verified extracted workspace with:

```console
cargo install --locked --path . --no-default-features
packetcraftr --version
```

## Frozen baselines

- Public Rust API: `319ac1647b8e40e9453178e418c40a26bfab98914df425b6e2c7dab1b8941762`
- CLI/schema: `{{CLI_SCHEMA_BASELINE}}`

## Qualification status

The exact candidate has completed the portable gate, security/resource/package
audit, privileged Linux and macOS live matrices, Windows x86_64 MSVC + Npcap
matrix, and four-platform portable byte-parity matrix. Downloaded-asset smoke
tests cover Linux x86_64, macOS arm64/x86_64, and Windows x86_64 MSVC.

Darwin cannot transmit an exact caller-supplied IPv6 header through a raw IPv6
socket because the kernel synthesizes that header. PacketcraftR reports this as
typed `capability.unsupported` before I/O; exact IPv6 transmission on macOS is
qualified through native BPF Layer 2 instead of silently falling back.

See the [platform matrix](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0-rc.1/docs/platform-support.md)
and [installation guide](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0-rc.1/docs/install-and-release.md).
Any failed RC verification remains a stable-release blocker and triggers the
documented remove-or-supersede response; RC artifacts are never published to a
package registry.
